76561198044233743,Recommended,301650,32755859,Posted: 24 June,all,SoupCanMafia,"Whether you are a US Astronaut piloting a Grizzly or a USSR Cosmonaut piloting a Golem, this is a review from when I started training up to the Mars missions.Story: As an United States-based NSDF commander known only as Grizzly One, your assignment was to protect the Moon from the invasion of the Soviet-based CCA invasion, ultimately failing, but getting everyone evacuated in time. Now, you have to go to Mars to establish a base among the CCA already stationed there, until you find evidence of an ancient alien race and their ancient tech that could make or break space forever. As a time piece game, it's a ""Cold War-gone-Hot"" based game with some 1984-level cleansing to make sure the public never knows and, to be fair, it's one of the better games to execute the story. 9/10Graphics: The graphics look pretty damn awesome. Playing it from a N64 version, the graphical advantage is apparent and it does do a lot of what it needs to do in order to be a redeluxe version of the 1998 classic. 9/10Controls: To me, the tanks control like lubed up bananas on a wax floor like they participated in the Indy 500 (which does make sense considering they're hovering tanks), but the controls for ordering your troops or base around to any potential power source works well enough. 8/10Music and Sound: Both are recycled from the original '98 version, but it would have been cool if the voice lines were updated with new voice actors, but add in the touches needed to make it sound like the originals. While I could just leave it at a 6.5/10 and get on with it, the fact that the music and a lot of the in-game sound can be replaced with mods is the reason I'll give it a 7.5/10.Overall and mentions: As a person who has only seen footage of Battlezone 98 and had some trouble with Rise of the Black Dogs on the N64, I was disappointed to see how such a hyped game resulted in something relatively obscure. It's not exactly a diamond in the rough, but it is definitely something like a ruby in the rough. I hope that it does get more players, though most people will still decide to download the original 1998 game. 7.5/10 because it's not a bad game, but it does have some issues that could make it overlooked. However, I still would like to recommend it to people so they can try it out for themselves."
