,Recommended,301650,33154490,Posted: 2 July,all,Half life Expert,"This nostalgia galore. Battlezone revived for modern computer systems! This is a dream come true for fans of this classic.If you played the old Battlezone from 1998, this will feel very familiar to you. The sights and sounds are practically the same, but the graphics are upgraded from the original release. There is little reason to not get the Red Odyessy as well.If you haven't played Battlezone before, here is the basic premise:In 1952, a metor shower rains down around the Bering Strait between Alaska and the USSR. The meteor remains, which are collected by the US and the Soviets, contain strange material that is named Bio-Metal. This material allows both superpowers to be able to make massive leaps in thier technology, far beyond even today's tech, although the general public is kept in the dark.Fast forward to 1969, and the Apollo 11 mission lands on the moon, Basically the Space Race as we know it still happens as a cover. The real space race is what the story focuses on. Before Apollo happens, the US has already established a military presence on the moon, using very advanced technology and vehicles derrived from the Bio-Metal. In fact, during the first mission, you see one of the Lunar landers.However, the USSR also lands military forces on the moon, called the Communist Cosmonaut Army (CCA) on the moon, and attack the US forces, which are called the National Space Defense Force (NSDF).   The story takes off from there, with missions taking place around the planets and moons of the solar system, not Earth though.  There is also a campaign where you play as one of the Soviets.Additionally, the Red Odyessy DLC, back then called an expansion pack, takes place on Ganyemede, one of Jupiter's moons, with the NSDF fighting the People's Republic of China, which has also obtained Bio-metal from meteors. Their space forces are called the Chinese Red Army (CRA). The Chinese have there own unique units, and are not completely allied with the Soviets, reflecting the real life Sino-Soviet split. There is one campaign for each side in this DLC as well.The game itself is a hybrid of real time strategy/tactics and first person vehicle combat.You control your vehicle and it's weapons, taking part in combat, but also command friendly units, as well as building bases and collecting Bio-Metal (the only resource, which can be found scattered about the maps or can be taken from the wreckage of destroyed units).Each side has a variety of vehicles, which you can change during a level. Hitting the 'H' key has you hop out of your vehicle and able to get in another one. You also eject automatically when your vehicle is destoryed. While outside the vehicle, you are basically an Astronaut infantryman with a plasma rifle. You are extremely vulnerable in this state.  So get in another vehicle ASAP.Don't fool yourself, This is a challenging game. This is from a time when games were more challenging to complete.If you are up for a challenge and want to try something different from more recent games, get this and enjoy yourselves!"
