76561198068172848,Recommended,301650,27982215,"Posted: 28 November, 2016",all,archofark,"I remember playing this game back in 98, it was the first ever PC game I remember playing. So having said that I preface with nostalgia having a factor here. The game looks pretty good for it's age, and unlike other games I have, playing on my 65"" tv isn't haveing any effect on the games frames.Pros:A very interesting storyInteresting units and tactics to play themTwo sepereate campaigns with provide their own challengesGood blend of FPS tank fights, with a healthy blend of RTS you can't forget aboutSimple and direct inputs mean you can just a few buttons quickly and get tasks doneLooks great (for being originally from 98), and still plays pretty wellBack in the day, the multiplayer was pretty fun, but it's been awhile since I played thatCons:Sometimes the AI is dumb as a sack of potatoes......When they aren't being dumb, they kick your♥♥♥♥♥In game doesn't really tell you nearly ANYTHING you need to know about how to play other than move and shoot, so expect to go to outside sources to learn how to do more complex manuevers, commands, and tactics.Unit limits - you can have 10 units from three categories (offense, defense, utility) so it's not quite a massive strat game as some others.Expect your units to have no self preservation skills, and they don't always like being called back to retreat either.So if the cons seemed a bit heavy, its because I want to be honest in this review. If you like RTS games, and like what you see it is worth it. The way the game feels even today is smooth and just like I recall from nearly two decades ago, whereas normally nostalgia games don't live up to their memory this one most certainly does indeed. Coming back to it as an adult I wonder how I ever played this as a kid, and where it's been all my adult life."
