,Not Recommended,301650,34448656,Posted: 23 August,all,CapoArgentino,"I am an experienced player of the original 1998 game and I still play it on occasion to this day. This is one of the greatest video games ever made and possibly the best tank real time strategy game ever made. It is legendary. Now onto the review of this Redux remake:First thing, I appreciate that they kept the opening theme of the game, that was a nice touch. The rest unfortunately needs work. This does not look much better than the orignal game with the HiRes texture pack installed. I was expecting the graphincs to be much more polished but I was dissapointed. The vehicles (Tanks, turrets, etc.) have been improved only slightly, they are still blocky/geometrical. I was dissapointed with the sounds (Gunshots, explosions) as well, they are the original ones and sound exactly the same. The explosion graphics look the same as the originals with the HiRes pack installed. A few more things worth mentioning: When you first open the game the small launch screen looks like the work of a 2 year old, very crude. The fonts of the in-game menus do not look good. Also, the original game has a built-in cheat code to enable access to all the maps. You would choose your side (Either US or CCA) and then type:  iamadirtycheater and the map list would appear. It doesn't work on this remake. Since it was part of the original game, it should have been included.I would not recommend this remake. Stick to the orignal w/ HiRes texture pack installed. Works and looks flawless, even on a modern system."
