76561198292631324,Not Recommended,301650,28820901,"Posted: 30 December, 2016",all,76561198292631324,"Battlezone 98 Reduxis a rehash of an old classic from 1998, brought to STEAM by Rebellion, a company behind such titles asSniper EliteorAliens versus Predator[1999, 2010].Battlezoneis a hybrid style game, a crossover between first person view vehicle combat shooter [FPS for short] and a real time strategy [RTS]. Does that mix do the job? Yes and no. What is certainly lacking is apause-and-commandbutton, minding the FPS element is often intense, leaving very little time to make grand strategic decisions. But whether playingCommand and Conqueryou have ever thought if it was you in one of those tanks, you'd show'em, here you go,Battlezoneis all about that and it is tough as nails.The game is a true classic, reminding me ofUFO Enemy Unknown[1993] in many aspects.BattlezoneandUFOare both innovative, experimenting and focused on multilayer management. Both also represent core science-fiction. WhileUFOis yet turn-based and general level,Battlezoneis real-time and down to the gunbattle.Battlezoneis definitely a gem of its time, probably even beyond its time, probably even beyond any time before or after its release, so to say. It is just a unique product. How does it stand nowadays? How playable it ultimately is at the present?That is when things come down to the rating, which unfortunately is negative. STEAM review must be either recommending or dissuading. With greatest difficulty I see this game appealing to modern [2016] players. The problem is more than just nature of visuals or lacking of certain ease elements, such as the mentionedpause-and-commandfunction. It is the oftentimes chaotic picture of action, difficulty of FPS combat and movement controls, overall difficulty level, complex real-time base and force management with flaws characteristic to the early productions standing for the RTS genre.The score is 5/10 wHATs grade. I should best repeat what has already been put in one of the other customers reviews: if you are prone to like this game, you probably already know it, thus have little need for any reviews to help you make up your mind about the purchase. Otherwise, if you hesitate, skip it.What is needed withBattlezone, is a complete remake [reboot], reintroducing the game to the modern public, instead of only a visual facelift [redux]. Currently it is a niche release, addressed towards the veterans of original version."
