,Recommended,301650,34563432,Posted: 28 August,all,Blods,"Absolutely the best computer game ever written - here with a beautiful face lift. No other game ever came close to combining a first person shooter, inside a real time strat with online play.  The flight mechanics were always fantastic, and you'd have fun just flying arounf the moon and doing sideway slides, but combined with such a clever and intuitive user interface Battlezone really hit all of the marks. The only thing that was ever wrong with Battlezone, was that because it was an unusual mix - most people never even tried it.So this is what it is.Imagine a strat game - in the style of things like command and conquer, or something where you're building resources and one or more enemies is as well. Now imagine that instead of being a god like figure looking down on that game, you're actually inside it. You can run around, jump into vehicles, eject and so on - but more importantnly you can still command an array of ships and resources as the battle rages around you - almost as simply as pointing at something.The AI of your ships and enemy ships is great and large battles can unfold - but then take that online - and suddenly you have a dozen people all doing this in a strat game, or simply battling it our like a roman gladiator.In the last 20 years this game is still unsurpassed in the in game user interface, flight mechanics, first person strat - and potential for online fun"
